In Tundra, if you want to compare two boolean values directly like in your 
code (cached.active), it will return a Syntax Error: unexpected token 'val'
'val'. In Tundra, when comparing two boolean variables or records, the synt
syntax is different from JavaScript/Python where we use "==" operator for c
comparison.

So correcting this issue by using "==", here is the corrected code:

```tundra
val cached = {
  active: false
};

val current = {
  active: true
};

if (cached.active == true) {
  print("send");
} else {
  print("skip");
}
```
